    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>No. 114.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Foote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 30, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the pleasure to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your No. 14, of the 13th ultimo, announcing the coming of a Corean embassy to
                    the United States.</p>
                <p>I confidently assure you that the President is much gratified at this friendly
                    action of His Majesty the King of Corea, whose envoys, Mr. Min-Yong-Ik and Mr.
                    Hong-Yeng-Sik, will be cordially welcomed by himself and the people of the
                    United States. Every consideration will be given to their wishes, and ample
                    opportunity afforded them to insure the successful accomplishment of their
                    mission to this country, both in the interest of that of Corea and those
                    amicable relations which we, as a nation, desire to cultivate with the Kingdom
                    of Tah-Chosun.</p>
                <p>I will thank you to properly communicate these views to the minister for foreign
                    affairs.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
